grid.events_cell-area-selection-start: It is only valid when mouse-config.area is configured. This event will be triggered when the cell area selection starts.
grid.events_cell-area-selection-drag: It is only valid when mouse-config.area is configured. This event will continue to be triggered during the cell area selection process.
grid.events_cell-area-selection-end: It is only valid when mouse-config.area is configured. This event will be triggered when the cell area selection is completed.

grid.events_cell-area-extension-start: It is only valid when mouse-config.extension is configured. This event will be triggered when the cell area expansion starts.

grid.events_cell-area-extension-end: It is only valid when mouse-config.extension is configured. This event will be triggered when the cell area expansion ends.

grid.events_cell-area-arrows-end: Only valid when configured with mouse-config.area. This event will be triggered when the selected area is moved in the specified direction using the Shift key.

grid.events_page-change: Only valid when pager-config is configured. This event will be triggered when paging changes.
grid.events_form-submit: Only valid for form-config configuration, this event will be triggered when the form is submitted.
grid.events_form-submit-invalid: Only valid for form-config configuration. This event will be triggered if the verification fails when the form is submitted.
grid.events_form-reset: Only valid for form-config configuration. This event will be triggered when the form is reset.
grid.events_form-toggle-collapse: Soon to be deprecated, please use form-collapse
grid.events_form-collapse: Only valid for form-config configuration. This event will be triggered when the collapse button is manually clicked.
grid.events_proxy-query: It is only valid when proxy-config.ajax.query is configured. This event will be triggered when the query is manually clicked.
grid.events_proxy-delete: It is only valid when proxy-config.ajax.delete is configured. This event will be triggered when deletion is manually clicked.
grid.events_proxy-save: It is only valid when proxy-config.ajax.save is configured. This event will be triggered when you manually click save.
grid.events_toolbar-button-click: Only valid for toolbar.buttons configuration. This event will be triggered when the left button is clicked.
grid.events_toolbar-tool-click: It is only valid when configured with toolbar.tools. This event will be triggered when the tool on the right is clicked.
grid.events_zoom: This event will be triggered later when the maximize or restore operation is manually clicked.
grid.methods_load-data: Loading data (may be used in table data that needs to be reloaded and in local increment scenarios)
grid.methods_reload-data: Load data and clear all status (for table data, reloading and partial updating of modified data are required)
grid.methods_update-data: Manually process data for manual sorting and filtering (may be used when you need to reprocess data after manually changing sorting, filtering, etc. conditions)
grid.methods_reload-row: Modify the line data and restore it to the initial state, for example, after editing, you need to modify it to the unedited state. Use only for modified data and invalid for newly added temporary data (it may be used in scenarios where row data needs to be saved locally)
grid.methods_reload-row-expand: Reload the expanded rows lazily and expand the content
grid.methods_reload-tree-expand: Reload the tree node lazily and expand the node
grid.methods_load-column: Load column configuration (may be used in table columns that need to be overloaded or partially incremented)
grid.methods_reload-column: Load the column configuration and restore it to the initial state (may be used in scenarios where table columns need to be reloaded or partially incremented)
grid.methods_refresh-column: Refresh column configuration (may be used in scenarios such as dynamically modifying attributes, showing/hiding columns, etc.)
grid.methods_create-row: Create Row,Rows objects (may be used when manual insertion of data is required in some special scenarios)
grid.methods_create-data: Create a data object (may be used in some special scenarios, the field name of the data will be automatically detected, and if it does not exist, it will be automatically defined)
grid.methods_insert: Insert temporary data into the table, insert one or more rows of new data from the first row
grid.methods_insert-at: Insert temporary data into the table, insert one or more rows from the specified position; the second parameter: row specifies the position, null is inserted from the first row, -1 is inserted from the end
grid.methods_insert-next-at: Insert temporary data into the table, insert one or more rows from the next row at the specified position; the second parameter: row specifies the position, null is inserted from the first row, -1 is inserted from the end
grid.methods_revert-data: Only valid when keep-source is turned on, restoring the data of the specified row or the entire table
grid.methods_remove: Delete the specified row of data. Specify row or [row, ...] to delete multiple pieces of data. If it is empty, delete all data.
grid.methods_remove-checkbox-row: Delete the row data selected by the check box
grid.methods_remove-radio-row: Delete the row data selected by the radio button
grid.methods_remove-current-row: Delete the selected row data of the current row
grid.methods_remove-merge-cells: Cancel the temporary merge status of cells. If it is an array, cancel multiple merges.
grid.methods_remove-merge-footer-items: Cancel the temporary merge status at the end of the table. If it is an array, cancel multiple merges.
grid.methods_get-row-seq: Get the serial number of the row based on row
grid.methods_get-row-index: Get the index relative to data based on row
grid.methods_get-vt-row-index: Get the index relative to the current data based on row
grid.methods_get-vm-row-index: Get the virtual index in rendering based on row
grid.methods_get-row-node: Get the corresponding row information based on the tr element
grid.methods_get-columns: Get the visible columns of the table
grid.methods_get-colid: Get the unique primary key of a column based on the column
grid.methods_get-column-by-id: Get a column based on its unique primary key
grid.methods_get-column-by-field: Get a column based on its field name
grid.methods_get-table-column: Get the columns of the current table (collected total columns, full header columns, full header columns after processing conditions, header columns in current rendering)
grid.methods_get-column-index: Get the index relative to columns based on column
grid.methods_get-vm-column-index: Get the virtual index in rendering based on column
grid.methods_get-vt-column-index: Get the index relative to the current table column based on column (the group header may be used)
grid.methods_get-column-node: Get the corresponding column information based on th/td elements
grid.methods_get-sort-columns: Get all column information currently sorted
grid.methods_get-checked-filters: Get all column information currently filtered
grid.methods_get-table-data: Get the data of the current table (complete full-scale volume data, full-scale volume data after processing conditions, table body data in the current rendering, table tail data in the current rendering)
grid.methods_get-row-by-id: Get rows based on their unique primary key (requires row-config.keyField)
grid.methods_get-rowid: Get the unique primary key of a row based on the row (requires row-config.keyField)
grid.methods_get-data: Obtaining data has the same behavior as data. You can also specify an index to obtain data.
grid.methods_get-recordset: Obtain table data set (obtain inserted, deleted, changed data, very convenient for adding, deleting, modifying and querying tables)
grid.methods_get-insert-records: Used for edit-config to obtain inserted temporary data
grid.methods_get-update-records: Only valid when keep-source is turned on to obtain modified data
grid.methods_get-merge-footer-items: Get the temporary merged table tail
grid.methods_get-current-column: Use column-config.isCurrent to get the current column
grid.methods_get-current-record: Use row-config.isCurrent to get the highlighted current row data
grid.methods_get-radio-record: Used for type=radio, get the currently selected row data, including the current list (if isFull=true, the full list)
grid.methods_get-radio-reserve-record: Used for radio-config.reserve, get the selected row data that has been retained, not including the current list (if isFull=true, the full list)
grid.methods_get-checkbox-records: Used for type=checkbox, get the currently selected row data, including the current list (if isFull=true, the full list)
grid.methods_get-checkbox-reserve-records: Used for checkbox-config.reserve, get the selected row data that has been retained, not including the current list (if isFull=true, the full list)
grid.methods_get-checkbox-indeterminate-recor: For tree-config and type=checkbox, get the row data of the semi-selected state, including the current list (if isFull=true, contains the full list)
grid.methods_get-row-expand-records: Used in expand-config to expand rows and obtain expanded row data
grid.methods_get-tree-expand-records: Used in tree-config, used in tree tables to obtain expanded nodes (note that even if the parent node is collapsed, it can be obtained as long as the node is still in the expanded state)
grid.methods_get-edit-record: Used for edit-config to obtain activated row data
grid.methods_get-selected-cell: Use mouse-config.selected to obtain selected cell information
grid.methods_get-cell-areas: If the feature is supported, used in mouse-config.area to get all areas selected by the mouse
grid.methods_get-active-cell-area: If the feature is supported, used in mouse-config.area to get the active cell in the area
grid.methods_update-cell-areas: If the feature is supported, use mouse-config.area to update the cell style of the selected area.
grid.methods_get-scroll: Get the scroll status of the table
grid.methods_is-edit-by-row: Used in edit-config to determine whether the row is in the active editing state
grid.methods_is-insert-by-row: Used in edit-config to determine whether a row is inserted temporary data
grid.methods_is-update-by-row: Only enabled for keep-source, to determine whether the row data has changed (you can also reset the edited data to the unedited state through the reloadRow method)
grid.methods_is-all-checkbox-checked: Used for type=checkbox to determine whether the column header check box is selected
grid.methods_is-all-checkbox-indeterminate: Used for type=checkbox to determine whether the column header checkbox is half selected.
grid.methods_is-checked-by-checkbox-row: Used for type=checkbox to determine whether the check row data is checked.
grid.methods_is-indeterminate-by-checkbox-row: Used for type=checkbox to determine whether the check row data is half-selected
grid.methods_is-checked-by-radio-row: Used for type=radio to determine whether the single-select row data is checked.
grid.methods_is-pending-by-row: Determine whether the specified row is marked for deletion
grid.methods_is-row-expand-by-row: Used in expand-config to determine whether a row is expanded.
grid.methods_is-row-expand-loaded: Used for expand-config.lazy, used to lazily load expanded lines and determine whether lazy loading of expanded lines is completed.
grid.methods_is-tree-expand-by-row: Used in tree-config to determine whether a row is in the expanded state of a tree node
grid.methods_is-tree-expand-loaded: Used for tree-config.lazy, used to lazily load tree tables and determine whether lazy loading of tree nodes is completed.
grid.methods_is-filter: Determines whether the specified column is in filtered status, if it is empty, then determines all columns
grid.methods_set-filter: Used for filters, options to modify filter columns (the updateData function can be called to process table data after the filter conditions are updated)
grid.methods_open-filter: Used for column.filters to manually pop up the filter panel
grid.methods_get-custom-store-data: Used for custom-config, used to obtain custom column setting information, used for server-side persistence
grid.methods_open-custom: Used in custom-config to manually pop up the custom column panel
grid.methods_close-custom: Used with custom-config to manually close the custom column panel
grid.methods_set-edit-row: 用于 edit-config，激活行编辑并激活第一个单元格；如果第二个参数为 true，则默认自动激活第一个可编辑列；可以指定列 fieldOrColumn
grid.methods_set-edit-cell: Used in edit-config to activate cell editing
grid.methods_set-select-cell: Used for mouse-config.selected, select the specified cell
grid.methods_set-cell-areas: If the feature is supported, use mouse-config.area to select cells in the specified area.
grid.methods_set-merge-cells: Temporarily merge cells, if it is an array, merge multiple cells
grid.methods_set-merge-footer-items: Temporarily merge the end of the table, if it is an array, merge multiple
grid.methods_set-row-expand: Used in expand-config to set the expansion line, and the two parameters set whether the line is expanded or not.
grid.methods_set-all-row-expand: Used in expand-config to set whether all rows are expanded or not (if all rows are closed, you can use clearRowExpand to quickly clear them)
grid.methods_set-tree-expand: Used for tree-config, set to expand tree nodes, two parameters set whether to expand this row or not
grid.methods_set-all-tree-expand: Used in tree-config to set whether all tree nodes are expanded or not (if all tree nodes are closed, you can use clearTreeExpand to quickly clear them)
grid.methods_set-current-row: Used for row-config.isCurrent to set the highlighting state of the specified behavior
grid.methods_set-current-column: Used for column-config.isCurrent to set the highlighted status of a column
grid.methods_set-radio-row: Used for type=radio radio button to set the selected behavior of the specified behavior
grid.methods_set-pending-row: Set the deletion status of the specified behavior
grid.methods_set-checkbox-row: Used for type=checkbox checkbox to set the selected status of the behavior. The second parameter is whether it is selected or not.
grid.methods_set-all-checkbox-row: Used for type=checkbox, set the checked status of all rows
grid.methods_toggle-checkbox-row: Used with type=checkbox to switch the selected state of a certain row
grid.methods_toggle-all-checkbox-row: Used with type=checkbox, toggle the selected state of all rows
grid.methods_toggle-pending-row: Toggle and cancel marking for deletion
grid.methods_toggle-row-expand: Used with type=expand to toggle the state of expanded rows
grid.methods_toggle-tree-expand: Used in tree-config to switch the state of expanded tree nodes
grid.methods_clear-merge-footer-items: Manually clear temporary merged table tails
grid.methods_clear-current-row: Use row-config.isCurrent to manually clear the current highlighted state
grid.methods_clear-current-column: Use column-config.isCurrent to manually clear the current highlighted state
grid.methods_clear-radio-row: Used for type=radio, manually clear the user's selection
grid.methods_clear-radio-reserve: Used for radio-config.reserve to manually clear row data selected by the user.
grid.methods_clear-checkbox-row: Used for type=checkbox to manually clear user selections
grid.methods_clear-checkbox-reserve: Used for checkbox-config.reserve to manually clear the row data selected by the user.
grid.methods_clear-pending-row: Manually clear data marked as deleted and restore it to normal state
grid.methods_clear-row-expand: Used for type=expand, manually clear the expanded row status, and the data will be restored to the unexpanded status.
grid.methods_clear-row-expand-loaded: Used in expand-config.lazy to manually clear the status of lazy-loaded expanded rows. The data will be restored to its unexpanded state and will be reloaded when expanded again.
grid.methods_clear-tree-expand: Used in tree-config to manually clear the expanded state of tree nodes, and the data will be restored to the unexpanded state.
grid.methods_clear-tree-expand-loaded: Used in tree-config.lazy to manually clear the status of lazy-loaded tree nodes. The data will be restored to its unexpanded state and will be reloaded when expanded again.
grid.methods_clear-sort: Manually clear the sorting conditions and the data will be restored to its unsorted state.
grid.methods_clear-filter: Manually clear the filtering conditions (if column is not passed, all filtering conditions will be cleared), and the data will be restored to its unfiltered state.
grid.methods_clear-cell-areas: If the function is supported, it is used in mouse-config.area to clear the area selected by the mouse. The cleared area can be specified.
grid.methods_clear-copy-cell-area: If the feature is supported, use mouse-config.area to manually clear areas marked for copy-paste
grid.methods_clear-data: Manually clear the cell content. If no parameters are created, the entire table content will be cleared. If a row is passed, the specified row content will be cleared. If a specified field is passed, the field content will be cleared.
grid.methods_clear-scroll: Manually clear scrolling related information and restore to the initial state
grid.methods_clear-all: Manually clear all conditions of the table and restore it to the initial state (may be used in scenarios where additions, deletions, modifications, and searches are required, such as clearing the table cache after data is saved)
grid.methods_reset-column: Manually reset the state of the column's display, hiding, and column width dragging; if true, reset all states (if the toolbar is associated, it will be updated synchronously)
grid.methods_reset-column_visible: Whether to reset the visible column state
grid.methods_reset-column_resizable: Whether to reset column width drag state
grid.methods_reset-column_fixed: Whether to reset column freeze status
grid.methods_reset-column_order: Whether to reset column sort status
grid.methods_close-fnr: Manually close the Find and Replace window
grid.methods_update-footer: Manually update the table tail (may be used in some scenarios that require frequent updates)
grid.methods_update-status: Update cell state (may be used when using custom rendering)
grid.methods_set-column-fixed: Set the specified column to freeze the column
grid.methods_scroll-to: If there is a scroll bar, scroll to the corresponding position
grid.methods_scroll-to-row: If there is a scroll bar, scroll to the corresponding row (may be used in some specific scenarios, such as locating a certain row)
grid.methods_scroll-to-column: If there is a scroll bar, scroll to the corresponding column (this may be used in some specific scenarios, such as locating a certain column)
grid.methods_sort: Manually sort the table (if order is empty, the sorting will be automatically switched)
grid.methods_is-sort: Determines whether the specified column is in sorted status, if it is empty, it determines all columns
grid.methods_recalculate: Recalculate the table. If true is passed, complete calculation will be performed (may be used in some special scenarios, such as hidden tables, recalculating column widths, etc.)
grid.methods_refresh-scroll: Refresh the scrolling operation and manually synchronize the relevant scrolling positions (for some special operations, such as scroll bar misalignment and fixed column desynchronization)
grid.methods_validate: Quick verification, if there are records that fail, it will return and no longer verify (except asynchronous verification); if the first parameter is true, the current table data will be verified, if row or rows is specified, the specified row will be verified or multiple rows. If no data is specified, by default only temporarily changed data, such as new additions or modifications, will be verified.
grid.methods_full-validate: The difference between complete verification and validate is that the current table data is verified by default and each row in the valid data is verified.

grid.methods_export-data_modes: List of ways to output data

grid.methods_export-data_sheet-method: Only valid for type=xlsx, this function is used to customize the cells of the workbook

grid.methods_open-export_modes: List of ways to output data
grid.methods_open-export_original: Whether it is source data (true is supported in some scenarios, such as virtual scrolling, optimized fixed columns..., if you need to support import, it must be set to true)
grid.methods_open-export_message: Whether to display built-in message prompts
grid.methods_open-export_is-colgroup: If present, headers with grouping structures are supported
grid.methods_open-export_is-merge: Supports temporary merged cells if present
grid.methods_open-export_is-all-expand: If present, force expansion of all tree levels

grid.methods_open-export_sheet-method: Only valid for type=xlsx, this function is used to customize the cells of the workbook

grid.methods_open-export_before-export-method: This method will be triggered before exporting
grid.methods_open-export_after-export-method: This method will be triggered after exporting

grid.methods_import-data_after-import-method: This method will be triggered after importing

grid.methods_open-import_message: Whether to display built-in message prompts
grid.methods_open-import_encoding: The encoding type of the imported file
grid.methods_open-import_remote: Whether to import on the server side
grid.methods_open-import_import-method: Only valid for remote=true, this function is used for custom import or server-side import, and returns Promise
grid.methods_open-import_before-import-method: This method will be triggered before importing
grid.methods_open-import_after-import-method: This method will be triggered after importing

grid.methods_print_modes: List of ways to output data

grid.methods_print_is-merge: Supports temporary merged cells if present

grid.props_auto-resize: Automatically monitor changes in the parent element to recalculate the table (may be used in scenarios where the parent element may change dynamically, show or hide in a container, or have abnormal column widths, etc.)
grid.props_sync-resize: Automatically following changes in a certain attribute to recalculate the table has the same effect as manually calling the recalculate method (may be used when controlling display/hide switching through a certain attribute)
grid.props_stripe: Whether it has zebra pattern (it should be noted that in the editable table scenario, the temporarily inserted data will not have zebra pattern)
grid.props_header-cell-class-name: Append className to the header cell
grid.props_footer-row-class-name: Append className to rows at the end of the table
grid.props_footer-cell-class-name: Append className to cells at the end of the table
grid.props_footer-cell-style: Add styles to table footer cells
grid.props_row-style: Attach a style to the row, which can also be a function
grid.props_footer-row-style: Append styles to table footer rows
grid.props_show-footer: Whether to display the footer of the table
grid.props_footer-method: The data acquisition method at the end of the table returns a two-dimensional array
grid.props_merge-cells: Temporarily merge specified cells (cannot be used to expand rows, not recommended for fixed columns and tree structures)
grid.props_merge-footer-items: Temporarily merge table tail (cannot be used to expand rows, not recommended for fixed columns and tree structures)
grid.props_span-method: Customize the merge function to return the calculated value (cannot be used for virtual scrolling and expanded rows, and is not recommended for fixed columns and tree structures)
grid.props_footer-span-method: Merge rows or columns at the end of the table and return the calculated value (cannot be used for virtual scrolling or expanded rows, and is not recommended for fixed columns and tree structures)

grid.props_show-header-overflow: Set all content in the header to be displayed as ellipses when it is too long
grid.props_show-footer-overflow: Set all content at the end of the table to be displayed as ellipses when it is too long
grid.props_keep-source: Maintains the state of the original value and is relied upon by certain functions, such as editing status, restoring data, etc. (it will affect performance when turned on, depending on the amount of data)
grid.props_expand-config: Expand row configuration items (virtual scrolling is not supported)
grid.props_empty-render: Empty content rendering configuration item, empty-render has a higher priority than empty-text
grid.props_params: Custom parameters (can be used to store some custom data)
grid.props_form-config_span: Number of columns occupied by the grid for all items (24 total columns)
grid.props_form-config_title-colon: Whether to display the title colon
grid.props_form-config_title-asterisk: Whether to display red asterisks for required fields
grid.props_form-config_title-overflow: All setting titles will be displayed as ellipses if they are too long.
grid.props_form-config_items_span: Number of columns occupied by the grid (24 columns in total)
grid.props_form-config_items_title-overflow: If the title content is too long, it will be displayed as an ellipsis.
grid.props_form-config_items_visible-method: The return value of this method is used to determine whether the item is displayed
grid.props_toolbar-config_buttons_placement: Fixed display direction of dropdown panel
grid.props_toolbar-config_buttons_transfer: Whether to insert the pop-up box container into the body (it needs to be set to true when it is embedded in a table or blocked in a pop-up window)
grid.props_toolbar-config_tools_placement: Fixed display direction of dropdown panel
grid.props_toolbar-config_tools_transfer: Whether to insert the pop-up box container into the body (it needs to be set to true when it is embedded in a table or blocked in a pop-up window)
grid.props_pager-config_pager-count: Show number of page number buttons
grid.props_pager-config_page-sizes: List of size options per page
grid.props_proxy-config: Data proxy configuration items (based on Promise API)
grid.slots_empty: Display template when customizing empty data
grid.events_current-change: Only valid for row-config.isCurrent, event triggered when a row is manually selected and the value changes
grid.events_radio-change: Only valid for type=radio. Event triggered when manually checked and the value changes.
grid.events_checkbox-change: Only valid for type=checkbox, event triggered when manually checked and the value changes
grid.events_checkbox-all: Only valid for type=checkbox, event triggered when all is manually checked
grid.events_cell-click: This event is triggered when the cell is clicked
grid.events_cell-dblclick: This event is triggered when the cell is double-clicked
grid.events_cell-menu: Only valid for menu-config configuration. This event is triggered when the cell is right-clicked.
grid.events_cell-mouseenter: Only valid for tooltip-config configuration. This event will be triggered when the mouse moves to the cell.
grid.events_cell-mouseleave: Only valid for tooltip-config configuration. This event will be triggered when the mouse moves away from the cell.
grid.events_header-cell-click: This event is triggered when the header cell is clicked
grid.events_header-cell-dblclick: This event is triggered when the header cell is double-clicked.
grid.events_header-cell-menu: Only valid for menu-config configuration. This event is triggered when the header cell is right-clicked.
grid.events_footer-cell-click: This event is triggered when the cell at the end of the table is clicked
grid.events_footer-cell-dblclick: This event is triggered when the cell at the end of the table is double-clicked.
grid.events_footer-cell-menu: Only valid for menu-config configuration. This event is triggered when the cell at the end of the table is right-clicked.
grid.events_sort-change: This event is triggered when the sorting conditions change
grid.events_filter-change: This event is triggered when the filter conditions change
grid.events_toggle-row-expand: This event is triggered when a row is expanded or collapsed
grid.events_toggle-tree-expand: This event is triggered when a tree node is expanded or collapsed.
grid.events_menu-click: Only valid for menu-config configuration. This event will be triggered when the right-click menu is clicked.
grid.events_cell-selected: Only valid when configured with mouse-config.selected. This event will be triggered when the cell is selected.
grid.events_edit-closed: It is only valid when configured with edit-config. This event will be triggered when the cell is closed in the editing state.
grid.events_edit-activated: Only valid for edit-config configuration. This event will be triggered when the cell is activated for editing.

grid.events_valid-error: It is only valid when edit-rules is configured. This event will be triggered when the data verification fails.
grid.events_scroll: This event is triggered when the table is scrolled

grid.methods_get-cell-label: Get the display value of the cell, supports formatter (except slots)
grid.props_keyboard-config_is-back: Whether to enable the Backspace key function
grid.props_edit-config_auto-focus: Automatically focus when cell is activated for editing
grid.props_edit-config_auto-pos: Automatically position when cell is activated for editing

grid.methods_reset-custom: Used for custom column function, reset custom column
grid.methods_toggle-custom-all-checkbox: For custom column functions, switch all
grid.methods_set-custom-all-checkbox: Used to customize column functions and set whether to select all

grid.methods_full-validate-field: Full verification, the same as fullValidate, the difference is that it is used to verify the specified column

grid.props_scroll-y_immediate: Whether to enable forced real-time rendering, the default is automatic optimization

grid.methods_get-tree-parent-row: Only valid for tree-config, used in tree structure to get the parent of the specified row
grid.methods_reset-filter-panel: For use in custom panels to manually reset filter panel conditions
grid.methods_save-filter-panel: For use in custom panels to manually save filter panel conditions

grid.props_resizable-config_show-drag-tip: Show drag prompt, display information during dragging

grid.props_row-drag-config_is-to-child-drag: Only valid when tree-config is enabled, whether to allow dragging into children of the target node

grid.props_column-drag-config_is-self-to-chil: Used for grouping table headers, whether to allow dragging yourself into the descendants column
grid.methods_get-full-columns: Get all columns of the table
grid.methods_get-full-data: Get the complete full body data, if it is tree-config, return the hierarchical tree structure
grid.methods_set-sort: Manually sort the table. If update=true, the data will be updated at the same time. Otherwise, only the sorting status will be changed.

grid.props_columns_edit-render_auto-select: Whether to automatically select the content of the input box after activating editing

grid.props_form-config_items_slots_extra: Customize the upper right corner slot template

grid.props_proxy-config_ajax_query-success: Method after the custom query is successful

grid.methods_get-form-data: Only valid for form-config, get form data
grid.props_row-drag-config_trigger: Triggering method, supports default default, cell cell, row row
grid.props_column-drag-config_trigger: Triggering method, supports default default and cell cell
grid.props_filter-config_destroy-on-close: Whether to destroy content when the filter panel is closed

grid.props_export-config_exclude-fields: Exclude which columns are not exported
